South Africa  added two uncapped
players, Duane Vermeulen and Johan Goosen, to the squad
travelling to  Australia  and  New Zealand  for rugbyâ€™s southern
hemisphere championship.  Vermeulen, a Western Province No. 8, and Goosen, a flyhalf
from the Free State Cheetahs, will join the 28-member squad for
the Sept. 8 Test against Australia in Perth and the Sept. 15
match against New Zealand in Dunedin, according to a statement
from South Africa Rugby Union today.  Western Province midfielder Juan de Jongh and Bath loose
forward Francois Louw, who has captained his English club, were
recalled to the squad.  South Africa is second in the standings after beating
 Argentina  in  Cape Town  and then drawing 16-16 with the Pumas in
